    "body": "Yes, I am aware of this. In my case, the limit seems to be around 500 MB per Anvil instance. That is around 3500 files. My point is that it does not seem necessary to me to write these logs on the disk at all if we typically need only a few previous state logs. Ideally, the number of state logs kept in memory would be configurable.\r\n\r\nThe current behavior still may wear out SSDs, especially in the case of high-performance testing/fuzzing.",
